<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?xml-model href="../../schema/HBAS_letters.odd.rng" type="application/xml" schematypens="http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0"?><TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="L041410.xml" xml:base="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/schnitzler/bahrschnitzler/letters" prev="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/schnitzler/bahrschnitzler/letters/L041409.xml" next="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/schnitzler/bahrschnitzler/letters/L041411.xml"><teiHeader type="text"><fileDesc><titleStmt><title level="s">Hermann Bahr – Arthur Schnitzler: Briefwechsel, Aufzeichnungen, Dokumente 1891–1931</title><title level="a">Hugo von Hofmannsthal an Arthur Schnitzler, [1. 2.? 1892]</title><title type="iso-date">1892-02-01</title><author ref="#pmb11740">Hofmannsthal, Hugo von</author><editor><name>Ifkovits, Kurt</name><name>Müller, Martin Anton</name></editor><funder><name>FWF - Fonds für Wissenschaft und Forschung</name><address><street>Sensengasse 1</street><postCode>1090 Wien</postCode><placeName><country>A</country><settlement>Wien</settlement></placeName></address></funder></titleStmt><editionStmt><edition>HBAS</edition><respStmt><resp>Transkription und Kommentierung</resp><name>Kurt Ifkovits</name><name>Martin Anton Müller</name></respStmt></editionStmt><publicationStmt><publisher>Theatermuseum, Wien</publisher><idno type="HBAS-L" n="410"/><availability status="free"><p>Copyright © 2017</p></availability><idno type="handle">https://hdl.handle.net/21.11115/0000-000E-870B-E</idno></publicationStmt><seriesStmt><p>Machine-Readable Transcriptions of the Correspondence between Hermann Bahr and Arthur Schnitzler</p></seriesStmt><sourceDesc><correspDesc><sender><persName ref="#pmb11740">Hofmannsthal, Hugo von</persName></sender><addressee><persName ref="#pmb2121">Schnitzler, Arthur</persName></addressee><placeSender><placeName ref="#pmb50">[Wien]</placeName></placeSender><placeAddressee><placeName ref="#pmb50">[Wien]</placeName></placeAddressee><dateSender><date when="1892-02-01" n="01">[1. 2.? 1892]</date></dateSender><context/></correspDesc><listWit><witness n="1"><msDesc><msIdentifier><country>UK</country><settlement>Cambridge</settlement><repository>University Library</repository><idno>Schnitzler, B 43b/1</idno></msIdentifier><physDesc><p>eh. Brief, 1 Bl., 1 S.</p></physDesc></msDesc></witness></listWit><listBibl><biblStruct corresp="HvHAS"><monogr><author ref="#pmb11740">Hofmannsthal, Hugo</author><author ref="#pmb2121">Schnitzler, Arthur</author><title level="m">Briefwechsel</title><editor>Hg. Therese Nickl und Heinrich Schnitzler</editor><imprint><pubPlace>Frankfurt am Main</pubPlace><publisher>S. Fischer</publisher><date when="1964">1964</date></imprint><biblScope unit="pp">15</biblScope></monogr></biblStruct></listBibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><langUsage><language ident="de-AT">German</language></langUsage></profileDesc><revisionDesc status="candidate"><change who="MAM" when="2016-03-04">Angelegt aus OCR</change><change who="MAM" when="2017-03-16">Durchgesehen mit Original in CUL</change></revisionDesc></teiHeader><text type="letter"><body><div type="writingSession" n="1"><opener><salute>Lieber Freund.</salute></opener><p>Ich bitte um die <anchor type="commentary" xml:id="KL410-3"/>gestern<note type="commentary" xml:id="KL410-3h"><p>Vgl. <bibl>A. S. <rs type="work">Tb</rs><space unit="chars" quantity="1"/><date>31. 1. 1892</date></bibl>: »<quote><rs type="person" ref="#pmb14756">Bératon</rs> kam mit der Idee einer Aufführung der <rs type="work" ref="#pmb31837">Aveugles</rs>. Damit zusammen eine Pantomime und <rs type="work" ref="#pmb30005">Abschiedsouper</rs> mit womöglich <rs type="person" ref="#pmb2362">Palmay</rs>, <rs type="person" ref="#pmb2446">Devrient</rs>, <rs type="person" ref="#pmb12948">Thimig</rs>.</quote>«</p></note> vergessenen <anchor type="commentary" xml:id="KL410-1"/><rs type="work" ref="#pmb31837"><hi rend="latintype">Aveugles</hi></rs><note type="commentary" xml:id="KL410-1h"><p>Ausschließlich diesen Einakter von <rs type="person" ref="#pmb12156">Maeterlinck</rs> übersetzte <rs type="person" ref="#pmb11740">Hofmannsthal</rs> in der Folge (<bibl>vgl. Brief an <rs type="person" ref="#pmb11666">Marie Herzfeld</rs>, <date>9. 3. 1892</date>, in: <rs type="person" ref="#pmb11740">Hugo von Hofmannsthal</rs>: <rs type="work">Briefe an Marie Herzfeld</rs>. Hg. Horst Weber. <rs type="place" ref="">Heidelberg</rs>: <rs type="org">Stiehm</rs> 1967, S. 23</bibl>).</p></note><space unit="chars" quantity="1"/><rs subtype="local" type="work" ref="#pmb31951"><hi rend="latintype">Bérénice</hi></rs> u. <rs subtype="local" type="work" ref="#pmb31953"><hi rend="latintype">Sept Princesses</hi></rs>.</p><p>Es bleibt bei Sonntag? </p><closer><signed>Loris.</signed></closer><postscript><p>Die <anchor type="commentary" xml:id="KL410-2"/><rs type="work" ref="#pmb31945">Überwindung</rs><note type="commentary" xml:id="KL410-2h"><p>Wohl wegen des Artikels <rs type="work" ref="#pmb32616">Maurice Maeterlinck</rs>. In: <rs type="person" ref="#pmb10815">Hermann Bahr</rs>: <rs type="work" ref="#pmb31945">Die Überwindung des Naturalismus</rs>. <bibl>Dresden, Leipzig: <rs type="org" ref="#pmb29771">E. Pierson</rs><space unit="chars" quantity="1"/><date>1891</date>, S. 189–198 (Als zweite Reihe von »Zur Kritik der Moderne«)</bibl>. <bibl>Erstdruck: <rs type="org" ref="#pmb29625">Magazin für Litteratur</rs>, Jg. 60, Nr. 2, <date>10. 1. 1891</date>, S. 25–27</bibl>.</p></note> habe ich zuhause</p></postscript></div></body></text><back><listPerson><person xml:id="pmb11740"><persName><forename>Hugo von</forename><surname>Hofmannsthal</surname></persName><persName type="pseudonym">Loris</persName><persName type="pseudonym">Theophil Morren</persName><persName type="namensvariante">Hofmannsthal, Hugo</persName><birth><date when="1874-02-01">01.02.1874</date><settlement ref="#pmb50"><placeName type="pref">Wien</placeName><location><geo>48,2066 16,37341</geo></location></settlement></birth><death><d